<br>
I have a Chardok Royal raid coming up and just can not find any info regarding what effect the changes have had. I've talked to a few in game, but seem to be getting conflicting info. I was hoping one of you that has recently done the royals would offer some advice. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I've heard that the Herbalist is in a new spot and there's no longer a safe hall. What is the effective method to deal with the loss of the safe hall?<br>
<br>
What order do you recommend killing the mobs? I've heard Prince, King and then Queen last. <br>
<br>
What the best place to whack them?<br>
<br>
I could really use any tips you have.<br>
<br>
Take care all,<br>
 <p><p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12811" style="text-decoration: none;">Kateki Cerberuss</a><br><a href="http://www.vitainfinita.com/" style="text-decoration: none;">59 Templar of Vita Infinita</a>
</b></p>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukateki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kateki</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/27/01 2:52:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umerkabaupon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merkaba UPoN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/27/01 11:25:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chardok Royals, looking for some pointers :)</span><hr size=1> I think your best bet is bring overkill and just keep moving. Never stop.  Respawn is to fast to stop.  King is pretty much a pushover and your best bet with the queen is to hit her with everything you got.  All melee use offensive disc and everyone ( clerics druids shamans ) should be nuking.  She has a killer AoE but has no resists and little hitpoints.  As far as where to fight them, we've just rushed them in their rooms and it's worked great.<br>
<br>
Good Luck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><center><img src="http://merkabaeq.homestead.com/files/merkabasig.JPG"></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umerkabaupon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merkaba UPoN</A> at: 11/27/01 11:26:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukayshasoulsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaysha Soulsinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/28/01 2:42:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chardok Royals, looking for some pointers :)</span><hr size=1> What about the 6-10 Royal Guards in their rooms? <p><br><A Href="http://www.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=30878"><IMG
