<i>The road to Heaven is paved with stones from Hell</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubordasen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bordasen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/28/01 11:16:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chardok Royals, looking for some pointers :)</span><hr size=1> You stop in the room before the Royal, have your monk pull as many of the guards as possible, then rush the room when the Royal is alone or with 1-2 mobs.  <br>
<br>
This is hardest with the queen, usually results in a number of monk deaths.<br>
<br>
Bordasen<br>
High Priest<br>
Second Covenant <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uultravoices.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ultravoices</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/2/01 12:46:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chardok Royals, looking for some pointers :)</span><hr size=1> Move *fast* through the place. It is linear, and the quick repops will bite you on the ass if you don't keep going. You should bring the strongest force you can muster. Fewer deaths=fast moving, because you don't have to rez half the raid after a pull goes bad. Move quickly.<br>
<br>
Prince is a pushover, he has some wimpy wind stun and small ae... it's the 94 guards in his room that make him a challenge. This is up to your pullers and your crowd control. Best bet it to pull off some of the guards and deal with them, and then pull the rest with the price when the guards are down to a manageable quantity. If you get the whole room, you may be fux0red, because there are so many guards and the chanters can't ae mez/stun with the prince there without attracting the undivided attention of the prince and thus becoming useless for much of the fight spinning in mid air stunned.<br>
<br>
King isn't too hard. Pull off some guards, murder until you have one or two left in the room. The chanters can charm their asses and use them to pound the king some. If he gfluxes, though, you may be screwed because you can aggro the room above, causing the Train From Hell to come hurtling to you.<br>
<br>
Queen, get her down to as few guards as you can, and then rush her with absolute maximum offence. she has no resists or hp to speak of, so everyone that has a nuke should load and blast away at her. Her ae is a large dot and unresistable. You can arrange your blasters so that they don't get the first wave of it though. the melee should rush, the casters union should follow like 3 seconds later. queen has probably unleashed her first ae by that point and if your casters stay at the threshold of the hall and her room, they can stay out of range of the ae. Blast blast blast and blast. if you have many fragile people in your group, word of vigor can save them, but if you do this as a fight not geared to maxiumum offence, everyone will die to that nasty ae. I repeat: she needs to be dead FAST. On the raids I've been on, she was dead before the 2nd ae one time and just after the 2nd ae the second time, and the third time it was really quickly after the first ae. <p><BR>
